Detailed Description

Ionic model for Rabbit Purkinje structure. Developed based on the paper by Corrias et al titled "Ionic mechanisms of electrophysiological properties and repolarization abnormalities in rabbit Purkinje fibers", American Journal of HeartCirculation Physiology, Feb 2011

  • Added Faster computation as suggested by Whiteley. We do Explicit update on Linear ODE and Newton-Raphson on Non-Linear ODE's.

Tusscher el ionic model for human ventricular tissue. Developed based on the paper "Alternans and spiral breakup in a human ventricular tissue model" by K. H. W. J. ten Tusscher and A. V. Panfilov, Am J Physiol Heart Circ Physiol 291:H1088-H1100, 2006. First published 24 March 2006

  • Implemented methods described in "Efficient Numerical Technique for the solution of the monodomain and Bidomain Equations" by Whiteleley. We can take larger time steps for Ionic Solve.

Set up parameters for Ionic model. We will pass these value to the Ionic Model Class. Enought to Create it once and pass a pointer to all Ionic Class objects. Makes it memory efficient. Used by Body Class For consistency this resides in the Ionic Class directory.

Purkine Model Tusscher Model Mahajan (UCLA) Model
